---
title: Game-Day Beef Chili with Cannellini Beans, Poblano Pepper, and Cheddar Cheese
description: Chili is a game-day-grub staple for good reason: it scores a touchdown with pretty much every person’s palate, no matter which team they’re rooting for. In this version, we’re heating things up with poblano pepper, cannellini beans, ground beef, and the dynamic spice duo of chili powder and oregano, then cooling it down just a tad with a dollop of sour cream.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/classic-beef-chili-e8652d67.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/classic-beef-chili-5a32a349c94eac72407d7d73-5971b805.pdf
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 730 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 49 g
  fiber: 16 g
  sodium: 1050 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/classic-beef-chili-5a32a349c94eac72407d7d73
time required: 30 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites
separate. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then cut into
½-inch squares. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%13.4oz can}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground beef{10%oz}, breaking it up into pieces. Cook, tossing occasionally,
until browned at the edges and no longer pink, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside.

Remove pan from heat and carefully pour out and discard any excess grease left by
beef. Return to medium-high heat and add scallion whites, poblano, and garlic.
Cook, tossing, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp} to pan and toss to coat veggies. Cook until
fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1}, beans, @crushed tomatoes{1%13.76oz can}, beef,
and 1 cup @water{1%cup} to pan and stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then lower
heat and let simmer until thick and stew-like, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and scallion
greens. Dollop with @sour cream{4%tbsp} and serve.

> Chili is a game-day-grub staple for good reason: it scores a touchdown with pretty
> much every person's palate, no matter which team they're rooting for. In this
> version, we're heating things up with poblano pepper, cannellini beans, ground beef,
> and the dynamic spice duo of chili powder and oregano, then cooling it down just a
> tad with a dollop of sour cream.